com.tsgrp.migration.event

Class InheritAttributesListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.InheritAttributesListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener

    public class InheritAttributesListener
extends AbstractListener
implements SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener
    This listener is used to:
    • pass some attributes and their values from a PARENT to its CHILDREN OR
    • pass some attributes and their values from the CHILDREN to its PARENT. It is most likely used if a node is loaded but one or more of the attributes need to be passed from parent-to-child or from child-to-parent.
      This listener takes in the injected associationNames list. If the the node has the association type (usually 'children') then it takes the PARENT node and evaluates if the PARENT has the attribute name of the injected attributesToInherit map. If the PARENT node has this value, the attribute name (value of the attributeToInherit map) and the value of the attribute on the parent node are added to the child node. If the 'parentInheritChild' boolean is set to true, the logic above is reversed so that the child attributes requested are passed UP to the parent.
